<subSubSection id="C3036525FFB9A22ADF62FA2AD5001AFE" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA636AEFFB9A22BDF62FA2AD7D11BA0" blockId="4.[813,1456,1428,2030]" box="[813,913,1428,1454]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636AEFFB9A22ADF62FA0BD51F1A3C" blockId="4.[813,1456,1428,2030]" lastBlockId="5.[132,775,823,1267]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BDF62FA0BD7ED1BC2" box="[813,941,1461,1487]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Rhipidantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BDF62FA0BD7ED1BC2" box="[813,941,1461,1487]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Rhipidantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has always been regarded as a monospecific genus endemic to the Uluguru Mountains of 
<collectingCountry id="F30E763EFFB9A22BD88BFA6BD1681BE2" box="[1220,1320,1493,1519]" name="Tanzania" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
. Its only species was originally described in 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BD83BFA4BD16E1802" authority="Wall." authorityName="Wall." box="[1140,1326,1525,1551]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Urophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BD83BFA4BD0B01802" box="[1140,1264,1525,1551]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Urophyllum</emphasis>
Wall.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B5FFFB9A22BD974FA4BD7251822" author="SCHUMANN K." journalOrPublisher="Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" pagination="55 - 113" part="28" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/210526" refId="ref9356" refString="SCHUMANN K. 1899. - Rubiaceae Africanae. Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 28: 55 - 113. https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 210526" title="Rubiaceae Africanae" type="journal article" year="1899">Schumann 1899</bibRefCitation>
: 57) before 
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B5FFFB9A22BDFACF9AAD0F51822" author="BREMEKAMP C. E. B." box="[995,1205,1556,1583]" journalOrPublisher="Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" pagination="200 - 227" part="71" refId="ref8668" refString="BREMEKAMP C. E. B. 1940. - Ist die Gattung Urophyllum Wall. in Afrika vertreten? Botanische Jahrbucher fur Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 71: 200 - 227." title="Ist die Gattung Urophyllum Wall. in Afrika vertreten?" type="journal article" year="1940">Bremekamp (1940)</bibRefCitation>
erected a new genus for it. Bremekamp separated 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BD871F98AD0811843" box="[1086,1217,1588,1614]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Rhipidantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BD871F98AD0811843" box="[1086,1217,1588,1614]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Rhipidantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BD94BF98AD1CF1843" box="[1284,1423,1588,1614]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Pauridiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BD94BF98AD1CF1843" box="[1284,1423,1588,1614]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Pauridiantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its (4-)5-locular ovary (vs 2-locular in 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BD8FCF9EAD17B1863" box="[1203,1339,1620,1646]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Pauridiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BD8FCF9EAD17B1863" box="[1203,1339,1620,1646]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Pauridiantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and from 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BDF62F9CAD7E61883" authority="Bremekamp, 1940" authorityName="Bremekamp" authorityYear="1940" box="[813,934,1652,1678]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Poecilocalyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BDF62F9CAD7E61883" box="[813,934,1652,1678]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Poecilocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its lax and pedunculate inflorescences, dentate (vs deeply lobed) calyx, sessile stigmas (actually connate into a style, though very shortly so in brevistylous flowers) and absence of conspicuous indumentum. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B5FFFB9A22BD883F96AD1C918E3" author="VERDCOURT B." bookContentInfo="414 p." box="[1228,1417,1748,1774]" editor="POLHILL R. M." journalOrPublisher="Crown Agents for Overseas Governments &amp; Administrations, London" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" refId="ref9498" refString="VERDCOURT B. 1976. - Rubiaceae (part 1), in POLHILL R. M. (ed.), Flora of Tropical East Africa. Crown Agents for Overseas Governments &amp; Administrations, London, 414 p." title="Rubiaceae (part 1)" type="book" volumeTitle="Flora of Tropical East Africa" year="1976">Verdcourt (1976)</bibRefCitation>
accepted the genus as distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BD8C0F94AD15A1903" box="[1167,1306,1780,1806]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Pauridiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BD8C0F94AD15A1903" box="[1167,1306,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Pauridiantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, chiefly based on the number of ovary locules, but the subsequent inclusion of 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BDF07F88DD78B1940" authority="Bremekamp, 1940" authorityName="Bremekamp" authorityYear="1940" box="[840,971,1843,1869]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Commitheca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BDF07F88DD78B1940" box="[840,971,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Commitheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(with 2- to 4-locular ovaries) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BD97AF88DD1EF1940" authority="Bremekamp, 1940" authorityName="Bremekamp" authorityYear="1940" box="[1333,1455,1843,1869]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Poecilocalyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BD97AF88DD1EF1940" box="[1333,1455,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Poecilocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(with 2- to 5-locular ovaries) in 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BD838F8EDD1401960" box="[1143,1280,1875,1901]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Pauridiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BD838F8EDD1401960" box="[1143,1280,1875,1901]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Pauridiantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes this character no longer reliable. In fact, on morphological grounds 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BDF62F82DD7F019A0" box="[813,944,1939,1965]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Rhipidantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BDF62F82DD7F019A0" box="[813,944,1939,1965]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Rhipidantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is even closer to 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BD829F82DD0B119A0" authority="Salvator NTORE &amp; Olivier LACHENAUD, 2019" authorityName="Salvator NTORE &amp; Olivier LACHENAUD" authorityYear="2019" box="[1126,1265,1939,1965]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Pauridiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto" status="s.str.">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BD829F82DD0B119A0" box="[1126,1265,1939,1965]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Pauridiantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57C7FFB9A22BD8B8F82AD16819A3" box="[1271,1320,1940,1966]" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" sensu="stricto">s.str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
than are 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BD9C2F82AD7CB19C0" authority="Bremekamp, 1940" authorityName="Bremekamp" authorityYear="1940" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Poecilocalyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BD9C2F82AD7CB19C0" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Poecilocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BDFF2F80DD07C19C0" authority="Bremekamp, 1940" authorityName="Bremekamp" authorityYear="1940" box="[957,1084,1971,1997]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Stelechantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BDFF2F80DD07C19C0" box="[957,1084,1971,1997]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Stelechantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(both of which are now included in 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22BDF62F86DD7F519E0" authorityName="Salvator NTORE &amp; Olivier LACHENAUD" authorityYear="2019" box="[813,949,2003,2029]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Pauridiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BDF62F86DD7F519E0" box="[813,949,2003,2029]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Pauridiantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and its great similarity to 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB9A22AD882F86DD5721D5C" authority="(Hiern) Bremek." authorityName="Bremek." baseAuthorityName="Hiern" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Pauridiantha" kingdom="Plantae" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="32" order="Gentianales" pageId="4" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB9A22BD882F86DD1EF19E0" box="[1229,1455,2003,2029]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="31">Pauridiantha insularis</emphasis>
(Hiern) Bremek.
</taxonomicName>
has already been noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B5FFFB8A22ADE0FFC86D6831D5C" author="NTORE S." box="[576,707,823,850]" journalOrPublisher="Opera Botanica Belgica" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 227" part="15" refId="ref9107" refString="NTORE S. 2008. - Revision du genre afrotropical Pauridiantha (Rubiaceae). Opera Botanica Belgica 15: 1 - 227." title="Revision du genre afrotropical Pauridiantha (Rubiaceae)" type="journal article" year="2008">Ntore (2008</bibRefCitation>
: 109). The fruits and seeds of 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB8A22ADDC5FCE9D64F1D7C" box="[394,527,855,881]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Rhipidantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB8A22ADDC5FCE9D64F1D7C" box="[394,527,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Rhipidantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, previously unknown, have recently been collected and also agree very well with the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB8A22ADC86FC29D5141DBC" authorityName="Salvator NTORE &amp; Olivier LACHENAUD" authorityYear="2019" box="[201,340,919,945]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Pauridiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB8A22ADC86FC29D5141DBC" box="[201,340,919,945]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Pauridiantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- the seeds in particular (
<figureCitation id="13222A2BFFB8A22ADE27FC29D6981DBC" box="[616,728,919,945]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[132,143,1134,1152]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,215,1096]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[793,1437,203,665]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 1. — Seeds of Pauridiantha chlorantha (K.Schum.) Ntore &amp; O.Lachenaud, comb. nov., from Jannerup &amp; Mhoro 129 (A, B) and P. gracilipes O.Lachenaud &amp; Ntore, sp. nov., from Lachenaud et al. 1981 (C, D) in electron microscopy: A, C, entire seed; B, detail of exotesta cells with outer tangential wall removed, showing thickened radial walls with small pits, and large pits in the inner tangential walls; D, detail of exotesta cells with outer tangential wall removed, showing thin radial walls with small pits, and large pits in the inner tangential walls. Scale bars: A, C, 100 µm; B, D, 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2653396/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Fig. 1A, B</figureCitation>
) are extremely similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB8A22ADDF4FC09D66A1DDC" box="[443,554,951,977]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Pauridiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB8A22ADDF4FC09D66A1DDC" box="[443,554,951,977]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">P. insularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B5FFFB8A22ADE88FC09D4851DFC" author="NTORE S." journalOrPublisher="Opera Botanica Belgica" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 227" part="15" refId="ref9107" refString="NTORE S. 2008. - Revision du genre afrotropical Pauridiantha (Rubiaceae). Opera Botanica Belgica 15: 1 - 227." title="Revision du genre afrotropical Pauridiantha (Rubiaceae)" type="journal article" year="2008">Ntore (2008</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 29). Therefore, despite the absence of molecular data for 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D2DFFB8A22ADC91FC48D5211A1D" box="[222,353,1014,1040]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Rhipidantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEABCFFB8A22ADC91FC48D5211A1D" box="[222,353,1014,1040]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Rhipidantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there can be no reason for keeping the two genera separate.
</paragraph>
